reviews.review: A lot of the old and a lot not explained but overall pretty good of combining the old with the new.  The movie contained some surprises in the plot. Some of the special effects seemed slack. It was still well worth seeing on the large screen in 3D about 4 rows back from the screen in a recliner with the wife.

Really enjoyed this movie! Don't know why it gets so much hate, JJ Abrams created an amazing ending of the Skywalker Saga. The visuals are insane but it was the audio that stood out for me (including the music). This is a movie you have to see more than once, which im planning to do.
One of the best star wars movies of all time. Pacing is faster than any star wars movie before it. It's not a perfect movie but it doesnt need to be for it to deliver.

This is by far the best Star Wars movie to come out since the original trilogy. While I will admit that it feels a bit rushed, I blame Episode VIII for this, as it did not stick to the established storyline. Therefore, this one had to move back to the story that was necessary AND tell the story it was supposed to.

That being said, it does a phenomenal job. Without spoiling anything, it ties not 3, not 6, but 9 movies together very well. The action sequences are worthy of the (good) movies that preceded it, the alliteration and references to the past saga are well done, and subtle enough that you have to look, which gives it much rewatch value. (Those who focus only on its relationship with Episodes VII and VIII will miss many of these.)

It's a thrill ride to be sure, and one that keeps you guessing until the very end. Especially when it's revealed that . . . 

No, I wouldn't do that to you. Go see for yourself.
